{"title_page": "Sopot, Albania", "text_new": "{{other uses|Sopot (disambiguation)}}\n{{Refimprove|date=March 2014}}\n\n'''Sopot''' ({{lang-sq-definite|'''Sopoti'''}}), is a small region in north-east [[Albania]]. It is also a village ([[Prrenjas|Prrenjas municipality]]) and mountain with the same name.\n\n==Geography==\nThe area has natural attractions for tourism, such as the [[Gostima Waterfall]], [[Karst|karstic cave]]s, woods, a rich flora and fauna, and local ethnoculture.<ref name=\"Republika\">[http://www.gazetarepublika.al/2012/09/sopoti-magjia-e-turizmit/# Sopoti, magjia e turizmit (in Albanian)]</ref>\n\nSopot rises up from {{convert|800-1970|m}} above [[Sea level#Height above mean sea level|sea level]], where the highest point is [[Gaferr's Peak]], {{convert|1972|m}}.<ref name=\"Republika\"/>\n\n==History==\nAccording to a folkloric [[legend]], during the [[Ottoman Albania|Ottoman invasion]] of this mountainous part of Albania, women with their children flew from the castle's wall so as not to surrender to the Ottomans.\n\nFollowing five hundred years of Ottoman occupation and [[islamisation]], the population of Sopot now carries two names, one Moslem and one [[Christians|Christian]].\n\nThe area's population has decreased lately due to immigration.<ref name=\"Republika\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Sopoti Librazhd]], football team<ref>[http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.club.sopoti-librazhd.2012-2013.3788..en.html F.C. Sopoti]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord missing|Albania}}\n\n{{Prrenjas div}} \n[[Category:Populated places in Prrenjas]]\n\n\n{{Elbasan-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Sopot (disambiguation)}}\n{{Refimprove|date=March 2014}}\n\n'''Sopot''', definite form '''Sopoti''' ({{lang-sq|Sopoti}}), is a small region in north-east [[Albania]]. It is also a village ([[Prrenjas|Prrenjas municipality]]) and mountain with the same name.\n\n==Geography==\nThe area has natural attractions for tourism, such as the [[Gostima Waterfall]], [[Karst|karstic cave]]s, woods, a rich flora and fauna, and local ethnoculture.<ref name=\"Republika\">[http://www.gazetarepublika.al/2012/09/sopoti-magjia-e-turizmit/# Sopoti, magjia e turizmit (in Albanian)]</ref>\n\nSopot rises up from {{convert|800-1970|m}} above [[Sea level#Height above mean sea level|sea level]], where the highest point is [[Gaferr's Peak]], {{convert|1972|m}}.<ref name=\"Republika\"/>\n\n==History==\nAccording to a folkloric [[legend]], during the [[Ottoman Albania|Ottoman invasion]] of this mountainous part of Albania, women with their children flew from the castle's wall so as not to surrender to the Ottomans.\n\nFollowing five hundred years of Ottoman occupation and [[islamisation]], the population of Sopot now carries two names, one Moslem and one [[Christians|Christian]].\n\nThe area's population has decreased lately due to immigration.<ref name=\"Republika\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Sopoti Librazhd]], football team<ref>[http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.club.sopoti-librazhd.2012-2013.3788..en.html F.C. Sopoti]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord missing|Albania}}\n\n{{Prrenjas div}} \n[[Category:Populated places in Prrenjas]]\n\n\n{{Elbasan-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SrpskiAnonimac", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sopot,_Albania"}
